  <ul>
    <h3>Let's See The Things Babies Love the Most</h3>
    <li>Babies delight in babies.</li>
    <li>Baby-friendly toys</li>
    <li>Engaging with them</li>
  </ul>
  <!-- Added more content to demonstrate scrolling -->
  <p>Music and Lullabies: Soft, soothing music or gentle lullabies can help calm babies and even aid in their development.</p>
  <p>Bright Colors and Patterns: Babies are drawn to bright colors and high-contrast patterns. Toys, books, and mobiles with bold colors and simple patterns can capture their attention.</p>
  <p>Textures: Babies love to explore different textures with their hands and mouths. Soft fabrics, crinkly toys, and textured books are often favorites.</p>
  <p>Faces: Babies are naturally drawn to faces, especially those of their caregivers. They enjoy looking at faces, making eye contact, and mimicking facial expressions.</p>
  <p>Movement: Whether it's being rocked in a caregiver's arms, swayed gently in a baby swing, or bounced on a caregiver's knee, babies often enjoy rhythmic movement.</p>
  <p>Peek-a-boo: The classic game of peek-a-boo never seems to get old for babies. They love the surprise element and the interaction with their caregiver.</p>
  <p>Sensory Toys: Toys that make sounds, light up, or have different textures can provide endless entertainment for babies as they explore and learn.</p>
  <p>Nature Sounds: Babies often find the sounds of nature, such as birds chirping or gentle rain, soothing and comforting.</p>
  <p>Interaction: Above all, babies love interaction with their caregivers. Talking, singing, cuddling, and playing together are some of the most enjoyable activities for babies.</p>
  <p>Mirror Play: Babies are fascinated by their own reflections. Mirrors can provide hours of entertainment as they make funny faces and interact with their own images.</p>
